               <p>Bedouin-type dialect</p>
            </div>
            <div type="general">
               <p xml:space="preserve">Redeyef is a town in the very west of the Tunisian governorate of Gafsa, and was, according to local sources, called Xanfūsa l-Kaḥla in older days.</p>
               <p>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="Redeyef-map.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/Redeyef-map.jpg"/>
                     <head type="imgCaption">Map of the governorate of Gafsa showing Redeyef in the very west</head>
                  </figure>
               </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">It is famous for the railway-line that was established for the transport of phosphate between Redeyef and the Eastern coast. This is due to the fact, that the town and its surrounding mountainous area is best known for its high amount of phospahte resources. </p>
               <div type="gallery">
                  <head>Impressions of Redeyef</head>
                  <link target="Redeyef-color-train.jpg">
                     <graphic url="Redeyef-color-train.jpg"/>
                     <head>Redeyef. Brightly coloured mini railway engine</head>
                  </link>
                  <link target="Redeyef-landscape.jpg">
                     <graphic url="Redeyef-landscape.jpg"/>
                     <head>Landscape</head>
                  </link>
                  <link target="Redeyef-Lampshades.jpg">
                     <graphic url="Redeyef-Lampshades.jpg"/>
                     <head>Lampshades on the marketplace</head>
                  </link>
                  <link target="Redeyef-roundabout.jpg">
